decision_details:
- the proposal made by Hon. Maithripala Sirisena, Minister of Health, to award the contract for the construction of radiation protective bunkers at the first five priority hospitals indicated below, identified for the purpose, to the Central Engineering Consultancy Bureau (CECB) at an estimated cost of Rs.1,103,061,593.82, was approved by the Cabinet:

	 	*	National Cancer Institute (NCI) Maharagama;
		*	Teaching Hospital, Jaffna;
		*	Teaching Hospital, Karapitiya;
		*	Teaching Hospital, Kandy; and
		*	Teaching Hospital, Batticaloa.
